@node Oscil "Basic 1: Oscillations and Vibrations"
· Free oscillations are when an object vibrates at its own natural frequency.

· Forced oscillations happen when an object is forced to vibrate at a frequency other than its own.

· Some display a particular form of movement called @{i}simple harmonic motion@{ui}.  For these systems, a @{"graph" link Kine} of displacement against time is a smooth sine curve.

· Damping reduces the @{"amplitude" link Wave} of oscillations.  Critical damping is where the oscillating mass returns to rest after one oscillation.

· When an oscillating system is forced to vibrate close to its natural @{"frequency" link Wave}, resonance occurs and the @{"amplitude" link Wave} of oscillations increase greatly.

· Uses of resonance: musical instruments, microwave cooking

