@node ElecMagI "Basic 1: Electromagnetic Induction"
· We picture a magnetic field in terms of @{"magnetic flux" link ElecMag2}

· The flux passing through a coil is the flux linkage

· When the flux linking a coil changes, or when a conductor is moved so that it cuts across magnetic flux, an emf is induced across the conductor.

· This emf depends on:

@{i}Straight Wire@{ui}

» The strength of the magnetic field
» The length of the wire
» The speed of movement of the wire

@{i}Coil of Wire@{ui}

» The strength of the magnetic field
» The area of the coil
» The number of turns of wire
» The rate at which the coil turns in the field

· The direction in which any induced current flows is given by Fleming's right-hand rule:

@{b}F@{ub}irst Finger  - (Magnetic) Field
Se@{b}c@{ub}ond Finger - Current
Thu@{b}m@{ub}b         - Motion

