@node Gases "Basic 2: Ideal Gases"
· Boyle's law:

» The volume of a fixed mass of gas is inversely proportional to its pressure, provided the temperature remains constant.

p þ 1/V or pV = constant

· Charle's law:

» The volume of a fixed mass of gas is directly proportional to its absolute temperature (measured in @{"Kelvins" link PQU} [273+°C]), provided its pressure remains constant.

V þ T or V/T = constant

· The pressure law:

» The pressure of a fixed mass of gas is directly proportional to its absolute temperature (in K), provided its volume remains constant.

· The equation of state for an ideal gas:

» pV = nRT

p is pressure
V is volume
n is @{"number of moles" link PQU}
R is the universal gas constant, 8.31 J/mol K
T is the temperature, in Kelvins
