@node ThermTrans "Basic 2: Thermal Energy Transfer"
· Thermal conduction happens when a metal is being heated.  The atoms at one end vibrate more violently.  The free electrons receive some of this energy when they collide with a vibrating atom.  The electrons move about and transfer energy to an atom when they collide with it.

· Thermal energy is transferred from regions of low temperature to regions of high temperature, using one of the following methods:

» @{i}Conduction@{ui}

Heat flows through a material without the material itself moving.

» @{i}Convection@{ui}

Heat is transported through a fluid material when the material itself moves.

» @{i}Radiation@{ui}

Heat is transferred by means of electromagnetic radiation, without the need for a material.

